  "text": "Whole brains or cortices were homogenized in ice-cold PBS, and immediately dissolved in 2ϫ SDS sample buffer. The lysates were subjected to SDS-PAGE and immunoblotting with antibodies to SNAP-25 (SMI81) and polyclonal antibodies to synaptobrevin-2 (P939) and syntaxin-1 (438B). To measure total SNARE protein levels, samples were boiled for 20 min at 100°C. SDS-resistant SNARE-complexes were defined as the immunoreactive material Ͼ40 kDa that was absent from boiled samples [CITATION_1] .",
